summary: Jodie Comer On Fashion, Insecurities And Inner Darkness
title: Jodie Comer On Fashion, Insecurities And Inner Darkness
excerpt: The Killing Eve star is killing it
description:
PWB (Phoebe Waller-Bridge): But you also express this powerful beauty. Every single person who works with you wants to talk about how wonderful you are to work with, and how the set comes alive with joy and lightness when you’re there. That’s also something that comes from inside of you, there’s a goodness and a fierce work ethic, without any ego. I want to know when it was you realised you were so fantastic?

JC (Jodie Comer): Shut up! [Phoebe makes an evil laughing sound in the background]. Do you know what’s played a massive part in that? My mum and dad – they’ve always been so ridiculously supportive, but also said, ‘This is your journey, this is all down to you.’
